Grand Street, north side, west from (No. 550), but not including Lewis Street, showing the R. Hoe & Co. plant, between Columbia and Sheriff Streets. The 3-story house (No. 550) shown on the extreme right, is a frame structure with a brick front. The Hoe plant was demolished in 1930, and replaced by a modern apartment dwelling, as a slum clearance project.

April 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

558-566 Grand Street, north side, east from and including Lewis Street. These are all frame houses with brick fronts. The view also shows 2-4 Lewis Street, at, adjoining, and north of the N.E. corner of Grand Street. No. 2 is a 3-story frame house.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

February 12, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
